Leverage is a key tool for understanding the robustness and reliability of multiple regression models, ensuring that unusual data points are recognized before finalizing analytical conclusions.[^write-a-text-book-section-explaining-the-concept-o-27][^write-a-text-book-section-explaining-the-concept-o-28][^write-a-text-book-section-explaining-the-concept-o-29][^write-a-text-book-section-explaining-the-concept-o-30] [^write-a-text-book-section-explaining-the-concept-o-31][^write-a-text-book-section-explaining-the-concept-o-32][^write-a-text-book-section-explaining-the-concept-o-33][^write-a-text-book-section-explaining-the-concept-o-34]

